WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:02.080
(upbeat music playing)

00:02.160 --> 00:03.840
(Rayanne)
Go now! Go!

00:04.760 --> 00:07.240
Um... excuse me.

00:07.320 --> 00:09.840
Could you spare some change
for a phone call?

00:09.920 --> 00:11.760
It's an emergency.

00:11.840 --> 00:13.840
See, okay, see,
this guy, like...

00:13.920 --> 00:15.280
Robbed our bus.

00:16.000 --> 00:20.560
Tickets and, um, you know,
my sister and I, we're twins.

00:20.640 --> 00:22.120
We're not the kind of twins
who look alike.

00:22.200 --> 00:23.640
We just finish each other's
sentences.

00:23.720 --> 00:25.520
Oh. That's cool.
How do you do that?

00:26.760 --> 00:30.360
Um, hi. Could you spare
some change? (laughs)

00:31.040 --> 00:33.760
She's... she's... upset.

00:34.560 --> 00:38.520
See, you look a little like
our mother, who's in a coma.

00:40.040 --> 00:41.040
(cries)

00:43.320 --> 00:46.680
Excuse her. She's hypoglycemic.

00:47.480 --> 00:49.880
I'd better...
get her some chocolate!

00:49.960 --> 00:53.320
(Angela) <i>So I started hanging out</i>
<i>with Rayanne Graff.</i>

00:53.400 --> 00:55.120
<i>Just... for fun,</i>

00:55.200 --> 00:59.200
<i>just 'cause it seemed like if I didn't,</i>
<i>I would die or something.</i>

01:00.000 --> 01:03.520
<i>Things were getting to me</i>
<i>just how people are.</i>

01:03.600 --> 01:08.000
<i>How they always expect you to be</i>
<i>a certain way... even your best friend.</i>

01:08.080 --> 01:09.920
(indistinct chatter)

01:14.960 --> 01:18.560
So then she admits she only joined
yearbook to be near Scott,

01:18.640 --> 01:20.760
which is, like, so low.

01:20.840 --> 01:24.920
I mean, It's just, I know,
if she doesn't want to be in yearbook,

01:25.000 --> 01:26.520
then she should, like, quit.

01:26.600 --> 01:28.880
(upbeat music playing)

01:29.480 --> 01:32.280
(Angela) <i>Like, with boys,</i>
<i>how they have it so easy.</i>

01:33.720 --> 01:35.280
<i>How you have to pretend...</i>

01:36.520 --> 01:37.960
<i>you don't notice them...</i>

01:41.320 --> 01:42.320
<i>noticing you.</i>

01:54.880 --> 01:56.360
<i>Like cheerleaders.</i>

01:57.480 --> 02:00.040
<i>Can't people just cheer</i>
<i>on their own?</i>

02:00.520 --> 02:03.200
<i>Like... to themselves?</i>

02:04.240 --> 02:06.640
So typical of the way she is.

02:06.720 --> 02:08.280
She always does stuff like that.

02:08.880 --> 02:12.040
It's not, like, too embarrassing
for me to know this. You know?

02:24.640 --> 02:27.240
-Who are you looking for?
-Nobody.

02:27.320 --> 02:29.560
(Angela)
<i>School is a battlefield...</i>

02:30.520 --> 02:31.680
<i>for your heart.</i>

02:33.600 --> 02:38.920
<i>So when Rayanne Graff told me my hair</i>
<i>was holding me back, I had to listen.</i>

02:40.720 --> 02:42.960
<i>'Cause she wasn't just talking</i>
<i>about my hair.</i>

02:44.440 --> 02:47.040
<i>She was talking about my life.</i>

02:53.760 --> 02:54.840
So it is you.

02:57.000 --> 02:58.880
I had my hair dyed.

02:58.960 --> 03:00.320
Oh, you had it dyed.

03:01.080 --> 03:03.920
I thought it had died
of natural causes.

03:04.000 --> 03:06.400
Angela, come on! I'm starv...

03:08.640 --> 03:09.680
starving.

03:10.880 --> 03:11.920
You're Angela's mom?

03:12.920 --> 03:15.440
Yes, I am. That's true.

03:16.480 --> 03:18.440
-I like your house.
-Thank you.

03:19.720 --> 03:23.760
-Who are you?
-Um, this is Rayanne and Ricky.

03:27.280 --> 03:30.160
You dyed your hair.
Okay.

03:30.240 --> 03:33.120
Uh, well, here is some...
cheese.

03:33.200 --> 03:36.480
And there are drinks in the,
um...

03:36.560 --> 03:37.560
Fridge?

03:37.640 --> 03:39.760
Uh, thank you. So...

03:41.000 --> 03:42.400
(clicks tongue)
Okay, I'm leaving now.

03:42.480 --> 03:44.080
Well, not the house, the...

03:44.160 --> 03:45.680
(scoffs)
room.

03:46.560 --> 03:49.080
-She's nice.
-Not really.

03:49.160 --> 03:52.520
-She took your hair real calm.
-That's 'cause you two are here.

03:53.760 --> 03:54.720
Good cheese.

03:57.480 --> 03:58.880
(exhales)

04:02.680 --> 04:05.960
(Angela) <i>I cannot bring myself to eat a</i>
<i>well-balanced meal in front of my mother.</i>

04:06.880 --> 04:08.600
<i>It just means too much to her.</i>

04:09.600 --> 04:14.680
<i>I mean, if you stop to think about,</i>
<i>like... chewing, what it really is...</i>

04:15.320 --> 04:18.320
<i>how people just do it...</i>
<i>like, in public.</i>

04:18.920 --> 04:20.240
Wait. Don't tell me.

04:21.440 --> 04:23.160
There's something different.

04:23.760 --> 04:25.680
I would never have died
my hair red.

04:25.760 --> 04:27.000
It's not red.

04:27.080 --> 04:28.880
-It's crimson glow.
-Ohh...

04:30.200 --> 04:34.480
well, I can see it now...
social whirl, wild parties...

04:35.160 --> 04:36.320
Axl Rose.

04:36.400 --> 04:39.400
(Angela) <i>My dad thinks every person</i>
<i>in the world is having more fun than him,</i>

04:39.480 --> 04:41.120
<i>which could be true.</i>

04:41.200 --> 04:42.720
What am I supposed to say?

04:42.800 --> 04:44.160
-Nothing.
-It's her hair.

04:44.240 --> 04:49.600
Exactly... and... we'll always
be able to spot you...

04:50.440 --> 04:51.280
in a crowd.

04:51.360 --> 04:53.280
(Angela) <i>Lately,</i>
<i>I can't even look at my mother</i>

04:53.360 --> 04:55.880
<i>without wanting to stab her...</i>
<i>repeatedly.</i>

05:00.480 --> 05:01.600
Hey!

05:03.080 --> 05:05.240
Who left all those lights on
down there?

05:07.360 --> 05:09.720
Oh... I just, uh, oop, okay.

05:10.120 --> 05:12.960
Danielle's still afraid of the dark.
She leaves the lights on.

05:13.040 --> 05:16.160
-I don't leave the lights on.
-Well, good. Okay.

05:17.240 --> 05:19.920
-I just...
-(Danielle) I don't leave the lights on.

05:20.000 --> 05:20.880
Okay!

05:20.960 --> 05:22.760
(Danielle)
And I'm not afraid of the dark.

05:23.600 --> 05:25.920
(Angela) <i>My dad and I</i>
<i>used to be pretty tight.</i>

05:26.000 --> 05:28.560
Um... how's school?

05:29.160 --> 05:31.720
Um, I'm starting
to like Anne Frank.

05:31.800 --> 05:33.640
Huh?
Is she a sophomore, too?

05:35.040 --> 05:37.040
-No. She's dead.
-Oh, right.

05:38.440 --> 05:39.920
Anne Frank, Dad!

05:40.000 --> 05:42.920
Oh, right! Right!
Um, I meant... I mean...

05:43.600 --> 05:46.880
Okay, Um...
don't stay up too late.

05:47.600 --> 05:51.480
(Angela) <i>The sad truth is...</i>
<i>my breasts have come between us.</i>

05:51.560 --> 05:52.600
(scoffs)

05:54.920 --> 05:58.600
Tell her not to walk around
in a towel, okay?

05:58.680 --> 06:00.960
-You can tell her.
-No, I can't.

06:01.680 --> 06:04.320
If I could tell her, I would tell her.
You tell her.

06:06.960 --> 06:09.000
Or get her a bigger towel.

06:09.080 --> 06:11.640
God, Chelsea Clinton.
Will you look at this?

06:11.720 --> 06:16.200
No freedom, no privacy,
constant surveillance...

06:16.960 --> 06:18.920
secret service men...

06:21.800 --> 06:23.120
-that's what we need.
-(chuckles)

06:23.200 --> 06:24.920
(crickets chirping)

06:28.880 --> 06:29.880
Patty...

06:31.920 --> 06:33.280
it could be a lot worse.

06:34.800 --> 06:35.600
I know.

06:38.400 --> 06:39.240
(kisses)

06:40.560 --> 06:43.760
I mean, she could be
cutting class, doing drugs...

06:46.360 --> 06:47.680
having sex...

06:48.280 --> 06:49.200
like we did.

06:50.400 --> 06:51.680
I never cut class...

06:52.520 --> 06:54.440
and you never had sex
in high school.

06:54.520 --> 06:56.760
You know,
I know why she did it.

06:57.640 --> 06:59.240
She did it to get me to react.

06:59.320 --> 07:02.080
-Maybe she did it...
-She did it to get a reaction.

07:02.160 --> 07:03.440
-Then don't react!
-I'm not.

07:04.640 --> 07:05.680
I won't.

07:15.360 --> 07:16.360
It's just...

07:17.520 --> 07:20.960
so hard to look at her.
She looks like a stranger.

07:23.920 --> 07:26.000
(dramatic music playing)

07:28.680 --> 07:29.720
(Angela)
<i>I'm in love.</i>

07:30.600 --> 07:32.920
<i>His name is Jordan Catalano.</i>

07:33.000 --> 07:35.320
<i>He was left back...</i>
<i>twice.</i>

07:37.480 --> 07:40.760
<i>Once I almost touched his shoulder</i>
<i>in the middle of a pop quiz.</i>

07:42.080 --> 07:45.280
<i>He's always...</i>
<i>closing his eyes.</i>

07:46.640 --> 07:48.640
<i>Like it hurts to look at things.</i>

07:48.720 --> 07:50.880
(indistinct chatter)

08:00.320 --> 08:01.560
(locker door closes)

08:19.640 --> 08:21.600
-Angela, get in here a sec.
-(door opens)

08:28.320 --> 08:29.440
Do you want to
have sex with him?

08:29.520 --> 08:31.320
-Who?
-Who?

08:32.000 --> 08:33.280
Jordan!

08:33.360 --> 08:34.520
Catalano?

08:35.560 --> 08:38.080
God! I'm not going
to tell anyone. Just admit it.

08:39.680 --> 08:43.000
I just like how he's always leaning...
against stuff.

08:43.800 --> 08:44.880
He leans great.

08:45.760 --> 08:48.560
Well, either sex or
a conversation... ideally both.

08:51.240 --> 08:53.920
Well, you have to come
to Tino's tomorrow night.

08:54.000 --> 08:56.200
-Angela, Jordan Cata...
-Shh!

08:57.920 --> 08:59.960
Jordan Catalano's
gonna be there.

09:00.040 --> 09:01.120
Shh!

09:03.840 --> 09:06.480
(Angela) <i>Rayanne always knows</i>
<i>who's going to be there.</i>

09:06.560 --> 09:08.520
(door opens)

09:08.600 --> 09:10.080
(dramatic music playing)

09:15.560 --> 09:18.200
I can't believe you did that
to your hair...

09:18.960 --> 09:20.160
without telling me!

09:20.240 --> 09:21.640
(bell rings)

09:22.840 --> 09:24.040
(indistinct chatter)

09:24.120 --> 09:28.000
(teacher) Take your seats please!
Come on! Come on! Please just...

09:28.640 --> 09:30.720
look, people, if we can't
get through this,

09:30.800 --> 09:32.360
the yearbook
won't have a theme.

09:32.440 --> 09:34.880
I don't really care.
It's your yearbook, not mine.

09:35.440 --> 09:38.320
Now, I'm going to read the themes.
Raise your hands to vote.

09:38.400 --> 09:39.880
We have graduation,
final frie...

09:39.960 --> 09:42.440
(Angela) <i>My parents keep asking</i>
<i>how school was.</i>

09:42.520 --> 09:46.200
<i>That's like saying...</i>
<i>how was that drive-by shooting?</i>

09:47.000 --> 09:48.720
<i>You don't care how it was.</i>

09:48.800 --> 09:50.880
<i>You're lucky to get out alive.</i>

09:50.960 --> 09:55.200
Apple, fruit of knowledge...
year 2000.

09:57.440 --> 09:58.680
Who didn't vote?

10:02.600 --> 10:03.600
Me.

10:06.680 --> 10:07.920
Where are you going?

10:09.880 --> 10:12.880
I don't want to be on yearbook.
Sorry.

10:14.640 --> 10:16.040
You mind telling us why not?

10:18.000 --> 10:19.000
No.

10:21.080 --> 10:22.120
I mean, yeah.

10:23.000 --> 10:24.760
I mean, I don't know why.

10:24.840 --> 10:26.120
(camera shutter clicks)

10:29.200 --> 10:32.040
-(Patty) Angela, Sharon is here!
-Don't they feed you?

10:32.120 --> 10:34.000
(Danielle) There's something
wrong with my waffle.

10:36.240 --> 10:39.400
-Sharon, no, don't eat the crust, homey
-I was eating that!

10:39.480 --> 10:41.360
It's got, like,
these little bumps on it.

10:42.000 --> 10:43.200
I left my Anne<i> Frank</i> here.

10:44.960 --> 10:46.560
If I find money, can I keep it?

10:47.360 --> 10:50.280
Oh, this room is a disaster!

10:50.360 --> 10:52.280
You could have told me
you were quitting.

10:53.400 --> 10:55.200
What? What are you quitting?

10:56.080 --> 10:57.080
We're going to be late.

10:57.680 --> 10:59.520
I thought you liked yearbook.

10:59.600 --> 11:00.880
(Danielle)
I found it!

11:01.440 --> 11:02.800
(exhales)

11:04.200 --> 11:05.960
Well, don't thank me
or anything.

11:07.280 --> 11:09.480
-Get out of my room!
-(mouthing)

11:10.120 --> 11:12.680
And when were you planning on telling me?
(scoffs)

11:13.280 --> 11:16.240
Listen to me.
"I thought you liked yearbook."

11:16.320 --> 11:20.560
Your room is a disaster. Do you think
I ever dreamed I would sound like this?

11:21.520 --> 11:22.720
Angela!

11:23.440 --> 11:25.400
I am not cleaning this up!

11:27.560 --> 11:29.240
(birds chirping)

11:29.320 --> 11:31.600
(bell rings)

11:34.240 --> 11:38.520
So, Ricky, Angela's in love with
Jordan Catalano. We have to help her.

11:38.600 --> 11:40.960
-Rayanne!
-Come on! I can tell Ricky.

11:41.960 --> 11:44.480
You got to come to Tino's
tonight. He'll be there.

11:44.560 --> 11:45.920
He doesn't even know me!

11:46.640 --> 11:48.400
Am I making a fool of myself?

11:48.480 --> 11:49.920
I don't know.

11:50.000 --> 11:52.000
Ricky,
give us the male perspective.

11:52.080 --> 11:53.640
Don't you love how he leans?

11:53.720 --> 11:56.960
I don't get obsessed with them,
so I don't have these problems.

11:57.040 --> 11:57.920
(bell rings)

11:58.000 --> 11:59.920
Oh, God! Second bell.

12:03.200 --> 12:07.440
I may as well go to bio...
since I'm not all that busy.

12:08.600 --> 12:09.760
(door opens)

12:09.840 --> 12:11.440
(dramatic music playing)

12:18.760 --> 12:20.240
(sniffs)

12:22.160 --> 12:25.680
And what is the purpose
of plasma?

12:27.240 --> 12:29.720
The purpose of plasma
is to...

12:30.720 --> 12:31.720
what?

12:33.120 --> 12:34.680
Why do we need plasma?

12:36.880 --> 12:39.960
-Brian?
-Because the league of nations failed.

12:41.160 --> 12:43.240
And why did
the league of nations fail?

12:47.640 --> 12:49.960
-Brian?
-'Cause it's written in the first person?

12:50.040 --> 12:52.400
Exactly. Thank you.

12:52.480 --> 12:55.040
Does she say 'she' was forced
to go into hiding?

12:57.520 --> 12:59.400
Somebody else besides Brian.

13:01.440 --> 13:02.440
Brian?

13:03.320 --> 13:04.600
-No.
-No.

13:04.680 --> 13:06.160
She says 'I'.

13:06.240 --> 13:08.480
"I was forced
to go into hiding."

13:08.560 --> 13:09.920
(light creaking)

13:10.000 --> 13:12.800
It's called the first person,
okay?

13:12.880 --> 13:14.320
This will be on the quiz.

13:16.760 --> 13:18.720
So how would you
describe Anne Frank?

13:19.960 --> 13:20.960
Lucky.

13:21.680 --> 13:23.160
Is that supposed to be funny,
Angela?

13:29.640 --> 13:32.880
How on earth could you make
a statement like that, hmm?

13:35.120 --> 13:39.360
(door opens and closes)

13:44.080 --> 13:46.600
Anne Frank perished
in a concentration camp.

13:47.480 --> 13:50.920
Anne Frank is a tragic figure.
How could Anne Frank be lucky?

13:51.800 --> 13:52.880
I don't know.

13:54.120 --> 13:57.480
Because she was... trapped
in an attic for three years

13:57.560 --> 13:58.960
with this guy she really liked?

14:06.920 --> 14:08.040
(exhales)

14:09.200 --> 14:10.800
(bell rings)

14:12.360 --> 14:15.160
Excuse my eating,
but with all these cutbacks,

14:15.240 --> 14:17.760
I don't really get a lunch break
on Thursdays.

14:19.440 --> 14:20.320
Sit down, Angela.

14:26.880 --> 14:30.560
(Angela) <i>Seeing a teacher's</i>
<i>actual lunch... is, like, so depressing.</i>

14:31.280 --> 14:33.280
<i>Not to mention her bra strap.</i>

14:33.360 --> 14:34.840
So...

14:36.480 --> 14:37.680
you quit yearbook, hmm?

14:38.280 --> 14:39.680
No explanation?

14:42.680 --> 14:44.000
Your appearance has altered.

14:45.520 --> 14:48.040
I'm really concerned
you're getting off on the wrong foot.

14:49.800 --> 14:52.320
Is there a problem at home?
(chewing)

14:56.960 --> 14:58.000
It just seems like...

14:59.600 --> 15:03.240
you agree to have a certain
personality or something...

15:05.000 --> 15:06.120
for no reason.

15:07.080 --> 15:09.240
Just to make things
easier for everyone.

15:11.960 --> 15:16.120
But when you think about it... I mean,
how do you know if It's even you?

15:16.200 --> 15:18.040
(indistinct chatter)

15:22.320 --> 15:24.800
And, I mean, this whole thing
with yearbook, It's like...

15:25.360 --> 15:27.960
everybody's in this big hurry
to make this book...

15:28.920 --> 15:31.360
to supposedly remember
what happened, but it's...

15:32.360 --> 15:33.840
it's not even
what really happened.

15:33.920 --> 15:37.120
It's what everybody thinks
was supposed to happen.

15:39.400 --> 15:41.760
Because if you made a book
of what really happened...

15:42.840 --> 15:44.840
it'd be a really upsetting book.

15:47.240 --> 15:49.280
You know,
in my humble opinion.

15:52.160 --> 15:54.560
(dramatic music playing)

16:08.600 --> 16:10.240
(Angela)
<i>My dad sells printing.</i>

16:10.840 --> 16:12.800
<i>It was in my mom's family.</i>

16:12.880 --> 16:15.880
<i>My dad was just supposed</i>
<i>to do it for a while.</i>

16:15.960 --> 16:19.000
<i>Then he was supposed to go</i>
<i>to chef's school, but he never did.</i>

16:19.080 --> 16:20.560
<i>I'm not sure why.</i>

16:23.120 --> 16:26.400
You should see what they
call chili con carne at school.

16:26.480 --> 16:28.240
First of all, It's just beans.

16:28.320 --> 16:30.040
-Well, It's not chili con carne.
-I know.

16:30.120 --> 16:32.960
-Con carne... with meat.
-I know.

16:33.040 --> 16:35.280
I think the lack of meat
is destroying America.

16:36.880 --> 16:38.920
(Angela)
<i>My mom took over the business.</i>

16:39.000 --> 16:43.560
<i>She's kind of my dad's boss now...</i>
<i>which I guess he tries not to think about.</i>

16:46.760 --> 16:48.000
Mom won't be home till late.

16:49.440 --> 16:50.440
You know...

16:51.320 --> 16:54.880
I think you give her too hard a time...
sometimes.

16:56.160 --> 16:57.520
She just wants you
to be happy.

16:57.600 --> 17:00.160
She wants everyone
to be happy.

17:00.240 --> 17:02.240
No. That's you.

17:04.840 --> 17:05.840
My point...

17:06.840 --> 17:07.880
I mean...

17:08.800 --> 17:12.480
think of all of the things
that she does... for you.

17:16.120 --> 17:19.240
Out of nowhere,
she'll get in this mood...

17:20.520 --> 17:22.280
and her lips will get all tight.

17:24.040 --> 17:27.960
It's just so obvious that's she's looking
for someone to blame.

17:28.040 --> 17:29.080
Yeah.

17:32.360 --> 17:34.440
But you know
that's not the real her.

17:36.400 --> 17:38.400
Just try to be nicer to her.

17:40.280 --> 17:41.440
Once in a while.

17:42.480 --> 17:43.960
-As an experiment.
-(smiles)

17:44.760 --> 17:46.240
-Okay?
-Okay.

17:53.880 --> 17:55.560
Dad, there's this thing tonight?

17:56.760 --> 17:58.440
At a friend of Rayanne's house?

18:00.400 --> 18:02.840
Like, this... rehearsal?

18:04.400 --> 18:08.840
Um, for this play that we might
all do as... extra credit.

18:09.720 --> 18:11.800
And I know mom says no going out
on school nights,

18:11.880 --> 18:15.640
but this is, like, part of school...
and I won't be home late,

18:15.720 --> 18:18.000
and I...
just really want to go.

18:21.800 --> 18:23.560
(rock music playing)

18:28.280 --> 18:31.760
(cheering
and indistinct chatter)

18:36.640 --> 18:37.840
